            <div type="cave" xml:lang="en">
                <head type="cave">Cave <hi rend="bold">51</hi>
                </head>
                <div>
                    <head>Description</head>
                    <div>
                        <head>Overview</head>
                        <p>In this central cave of section C only one part of the “Chapter on Sacred
                            Practice” from the <hi rend="italic">Nirvana Sutra</hi> is engraved on
                            wall f. On wall a is the colophon of 723 by donor Yang Yi, and on wall f
                            are the two colophons by donor Wang Yuanzhao, dated 959 and 961.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <head>Location</head>
                        <list>
                            <item>Southern slope, the central cave of the tripartite group of caves
                                    <hi rend="bold">46</hi>, <hi rend="bold">51</hi>, and <hi rend="bold">58</hi> in section C, ca. 400 cm above present
                                walkway. </item>
                            <item>Width of the wall between the openings at the front of caves <hi rend="bold">46</hi> and <hi rend="bold">51</hi>: 172 cm.</item>
                            <item>Width of the wall between the openings at the front of caves <hi rend="bold">51</hi> and <hi rend="bold">58</hi>: 117 cm.</item>
                            <item>Direction: wall d 318°, wall f 308°.</item>
                        </list>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <head>Shape</head>
                        <list>
                            <item>Box-shaped with open front; an approximately square ground plan
                                widens towards the rear; the horizontal ceiling rises towards the
                                rear.</item>
                        </list>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <head>Measurements</head>
                        <list>
                            <item>Wall a: height 273 cm, width 60 cm (from entrance opening to the
                                standing Buddha figure <hi rend="bold">49</hi>).</item>
                            <item>Wall d: height at the front 338 cm, at the rear 360 cm, width 320
                                cm.</item>
                            <item>Wall e: height at western corner 360 cm, height at eastern corner
                                358 cm, width 371 cm.</item>
                            <item>Wall f: height at the front 340 cm, at the rear 358, width 354
                                cm.</item>
                            <item>Width of opening 255 cm.</item>
                        </list>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <head>Changes</head>
                        <p>On the walls, just inside the entrance, and in the ceiling above, are 10
                            cm wide incisions. Their distance to the rear of the cave is 280 cm on
                            wall d, and 267 cm on wall f. These incisions probably secured wooden or
                            stone thresholds when the cave was occupied during the 1960s.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div xml:id="Site_WFY_Section_Cb_Cave51_d_en">
                        <head>Wall d</head>
                        <p>A polished area of irregular shape, ca. 90–225 cm above the ground,
                            extends from the entrance corner to a maximum width of 57 cm. It
                            contains about a dozen graffiti, among them the one by Renunciant
                            Xuanying. A second polished area, 158 x 160 cm, begins 146 cm from the
                            entrance, and 45–58 cm from the ceiling; it ends 152 cm above the floor,
                            and 10 cm from the rear wall e. No engraving. Some later graffiti,
                            engraved and also written in ink.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div xml:id="Site_WFY_Section_Cb_Cave51_e_en">
                        <head>Wall e</head>
                        <p>No polished area, no engraving.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div xml:id="Site_WFY_Section_Cb_Cave51_f_en">
                        <head>Wall f</head>
                        <div>
                            <head>Layout</head>
                            <list>
                                <item>A polished area, 301 x 338 cm, begins ca. 1– 20 cm from wall e
                                    and 22 cm below the ceiling; it ends 29–34 cm, and near the
                                    entrance 17 cm, above the floor.</item>
                                <item>The field of script, like that in the rear of wall d, is a
                                    vertical rectangle, 290.5 x 130.5 cm. It begins 55 to 60 cm from
                                    wall e and ca. 25 cm below the ceiling; it ends 32 cm above the
                                    floor and 195 cm from the entrance; the lower edge is
                                    approximately horizontal.</item>
                            </list>
                        </div>
