                    <div>
                        <head>State of preservation</head>
                        <p>Generally good. The surface is not even; a horizontal crack extends ca.
                            103 cm above the floor. It results from geological layers with clay
                            galls that are seen in all three caves of section C and elsewhere in the
                            Grove. Here these galls create gaps from columns 3–13 and 45–49; two
                            round man-made holes, with a diameter of 3–4 cm, were hewn 125 cm above
                            the floor, in columns 6–7, and, 183 cm above the floor, in columns
                            18–19. A black stain covers the upper part toward the entrance. The 2–3
                            lowest rows are covered by a band of black lichen that runs over the
                            width of the entire wall.</p>
